<p>The <code>pad</code> tag processes PAD template content.</p>

<h2>Basic PAD Tag</h2>
<pre>{open}pad{close}
  Template content: {open}$items{close} items
{open}/pad{close}</pre>
{pad}
  <p>Template content processed</p>
{/pad}

<h2>PAD with Data</h2>
<pre>{open}data 'myData'{close}
  [ {open}"text": "First"{close}, {open}"text": "Second"{close} ]
{open}/data{close}

{open}pad data='myData'{close}
  @start@
    Item: {open}$text{close}
  @end@
{open}/pad{close}</pre>
{data 'myData'}
  [ {"text": "First"}, {"text": "Second"} ]
{/data}
{pad data='myData'}
  @start@
  <p>Item: {$text}</p>
  @end@
{/pad}

<h2>PAD with Variable Assignment</h2>
<pre>{open}pad $color='blue'{close}
  Color is: {open}$color{close}
{open}/pad{close}</pre>
{pad $color='blue'}
  <p>Color is: {$color}</p>
{/pad}

<h2>Iteration with @start@ @end@</h2>
<p>The @start@ and @end@ markers define the iteration block:</p>
<ul>
{pad data='myData'}
  @start@
  <li>{$text}</li>
  @end@
{/pad}
</ul>
